#. Default: "High-performance sites will often place a caching reverse proxy such as Varnish or a CDN in front of Zope. The caching operations configured elsewhere on this screen can often take advantage of such a proxy by instructing it to cache certain content in a certain way, whilst passing requests for other content through to Plone always. Plone can also send so-called <code>PURGE</code> requests to a caching proxy when content changes, reducing the risk of a stale response from a cached copy."
